# Ultracite Lint Conventions

This project uses Ultracite (Biome) — not ESLint or Prettier.

## Key rules to follow

- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Add `type="button"` to all `<button>` elements
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` or proper types
- Never use `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()`
- Use `===` not `==`
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassigning
- No unused variables or imports
- Double quotes for strings, semicolons required

## After writing code

Run `bunx ultracite check` to validate. Fix issues with `bunx ultracite fix`.

## Suppressing a rule

```tsx
// biome-ignore lint/category/ruleName: justification here
```
